   -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Shell - Program to get commands from keyboard- Sends them to the OS.
   bash - Bourne again shell
   
   
   Commands - 
   
   echo -> prints 
   date -> prints current date
   whoami -> prints the user name
   pwd -> current working directory - Print working directory 
   
   cd -> change directory  
      cd . -> current directory
      cd .. -> parent directory
      cd ~ -> home directory
      cd - -> previous directory
      cd -> home directory
      
   ls -> list directories
      ls -a ->  to show hidden files (starts with .)
      ls -l -> detaileed view
      ls -al -> union of above
      ls -R -> recursive
      ls -r -> reverse orde
      ls -t -> sort by modification time
  
   touch -> to create empty files
   file -> to find the type of the file
   cat -> to read a file - can take multiple files too
   less -> paged view 
        q  -> quit
        /<word> -> search for the word
        
   history -> all prev commands entered
   
   cp -> copy file to directory
        cp a* /home/copydir 
        cp -r sourcedir/ /home/desktop/targetdir
        cp -i -> prompts if same file name exists
   mv -> move - rename file
        mv -b -> if same file name exists it creaates a new file with a ~
   
   mkdir -> make directories
        mkdir -p <path> -> to create sub directories
   
   rm -> remove
        rm -f -> delete without any restrictions
        rm -i -> gives prompt
        rm -r -> remove directory and subdirs
        rmdir -> remove directory
        
   find 
        find </dir> -name <filename>
        find </dir> -type d -name <dirname> -> d for directory
   help
        help <command>
   man - manual
        man <command>
   whatis
        whatis <command>
        
    alias 
        alias <variable>='<command>' -> variable can be used instead of the whole command
        unalias <variable> -> delete the alias 
    
    exit -> exit from shell
    logout -> logout current user
    
   
   
   
   
